longBusinessSummary: Schweizer Electronic AG, together with its subsidiaries, develops, produces, and distributes printed circuit boards (PCBs) worldwide. The company offers sportive PCBs; and power electronics, including heavy copper, inlay, power combi, and IMS boards. It also provides embedding products and solutions, such as integrated interposer board for the embedding of logic semiconductors; power PCB; cavity boards for various solutions; and ÂµÂ² Pack for smallest, thinnest, and multi-chip semiconductor packages, as well as modules with direct pad contacting. In addition, the company offers system cost reduction solutions, including FR4 Flex with restricted installation possibilities; resistor print for integration of resistors as a passive component through thick-film technology carried out by screen printing process; high frequency PCBs for safety engineering for vehicles; electroless nickel-electroless palladium-autocatalytic gold surface finishes for automotive and industrial applications; and all in one PCBs for power electronics, embedding, and system cost reduction applications. It provides its products for the automotive, solar, aviation, and general industries; and electronic control units, motor drives, DC/DC and AC/DC converters, and consumer and mobile applications, as well as semiconductor packaging. Schweizer Electronic AG was founded in 1849 and is headquartered in Schramberg, Germany.
